      public Transaction(Integer idSecurityaccount, Cashaccount cashAccount, Security security, Double units, Double quotation, TransactionType transactionType, Double taxCost, Double transactionCost, Double accruedInterest, Date transactionTime, Double currencyExRate)

    • Transaction

      public Transaction(Integer idSecurityaccount, Cashaccount cashAccount, Security security, Double cashaccountAmount, Double units, Double quotation, TransactionType transactionType, Double taxCost, Double transactionCost, Double assetInvestmentValue1, Date transactionTime, Double currencyExRate, Integer idCurrencypair, Date exDate, Boolean taxableInterest)
      Main constructor for creating comprehensive security transactions with all possible parameters. Used for transactions involving securities, currency exchanges, and various costs.
      Parameters:
      idSecurityaccount - the security account ID for the transaction
      cashAccount - the cash account affected by the transaction
      security - the security being traded (null for cash-only transactions)
      cashaccountAmount - the amount credited/debited to the cash account (calculated if null)
      units - the number of units traded (shares, contracts, etc.)
      quotation - the price per unit of the security
      transactionType - the type of transaction (buy, sell, dividend, etc.)
      taxCost - any taxes associated with the transaction
      transactionCost - any transaction fees or costs
      assetInvestmentValue1 - accrued interest for bonds or daily holding costs for CFDs
      transactionTime - the date and time when the transaction occurred
      currencyExRate - exchange rate if transaction involves currency conversion
      idCurrencypair - currency pair ID used with the exchange rate
      exDate - ex-dividend date for dividend transactions
      taxableInterest - whether interest/dividend is subject to taxation

      public double getExchangeRateOnCurrency(String mc, DateTransactionCurrencypairMap dateTransactionCurrencyMap)
      Determines the exchange rate to apply when converting from the cash account currency to the specified main currency. Handles various currency scenarios including security and cash account currency differences.
      Parameters:
      mc - the main currency to convert to
      dateTransactionCurrencyMap - currency mapping context for rate lookups
      Returns:
      exchange rate from cash account currency to main currency

      public void clearAccountTransaction()
      Clears transaction-specific fields based on the transaction type to ensure data consistency. Removes fields that are not applicable for certain types of cash account transactions like fees, deposits, interest, and withdrawals.

    • calcCostTaxMaybeBasePrice

      public double calcCostTaxMaybeBasePrice(String mc, SecurityCostPosition securityCostPosition, DateTransactionCurrencypairMap dateTransactionCurrencyMap, boolean calcBasePrice)
      Calculates cost and tax amounts in the main currency and optionally computes the base price. Converts transaction costs and tax costs using appropriate exchange rates and populates the security cost position object with the calculated values.
      Parameters:
      mc - the main currency for conversions
      securityCostPosition - the cost position object to populate with calculated values
      dateTransactionCurrencyMap - currency mapping context for exchange rate lookups
      calcBasePrice - whether to calculate the base price for transaction costs
      Returns:
      the base price for transaction costs in main currency if calculated, 0.0 otherwise

    • validateCashaccountAmount

      public void validateCashaccountAmount(Transaction openPositionMarginTransaction, Integer currencyFraction)
      Validates that the cash account amount matches the calculated amount based on transaction details. Performs different validation logic for margin instruments versus general securities and can optionally auto-correct small discrepancies by adjusting quotation or exchange rate.
      Parameters:
      openPositionMarginTransaction - the original margin position transaction (for margin closures)
      currencyFraction - the number of decimal places for currency rounding
      Throws:
      DataViolationException - if calculated amount doesn't match the recorded amount
